---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Markdown Negotiation For Agents | Is It Agent Ready?"
  description="Learn how to return markdown from HTML pages when agents request `Accept: text/markdown`, reducing tokens and improving agent comprehension."
  canonical="https://isitagentready.com/checks/markdown-negotiation"
>
  <section class="card" style="padding: 28px;">
    <h1 class="section-title">Markdown negotiation</h1>
    <p class="muted">
      Agent-ready websites should return markdown when an AI system requests `Accept: text/markdown`. This reduces token cost and helps agents extract the actual content instead of parsing dense HTML.
    </p>
    <h2>What a passing result looks like</h2>
    <pre>{`GET / HTTP/1.1
Accept: text/markdown

HTTP/1.1 200 OK
Content-Type: text/markdown; charset=utf-8`}</pre>
    <h2>Implementation guidance</h2>
    <ul class="clean">
      <li>Keep HTML as the default for browsers.</li>
      <li>Return markdown only when the request explicitly asks for it.</li>
      <li>Make sure `Content-Type` is actually `text/markdown`.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="muted">
      Reference:
      <a class="link" href="https://developers.cloudflare.com/fundamentals/reference/markdown-for-agents/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"> Markdown for Agents</a>
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
